org.onyxplatform.api.java.utils

Class MapFns

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.onyxplatform.api.java.utils.MapFns
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OnyxNames

    public class MapFns
extends java.lang.Object
implements OnyxNames
    MapFns is a static utility class used to operate on the main data type used by Onyx, the IPersistentMap. It is useful for translating between Java type maps, loading IPersistentMaps from resource files, and manipulating the maps using functions like get-in(getting a nested value from a nested key), assoc (associating a new entry to the map), etc.

      • getIn

        public static clojure.lang.IPersistentMap getIn(clojure.lang.IPersistentMap m,
                                                java.lang.String... keys)
        Similar to get, but retrieves a nested value for the given keys. For example, if the map had three levels, with a top level key "1", and "1" value was another map with a value "2", and "2" was another map with a value "3", this method could get the value for "3" by using get-in(map, "1", "2", "3")
        Parameters:
        m - The map holding the key-values to search
        keys - The set of keys describing the chain of retrieval holding the desired value
        Returns:
        The value held by the specified key chain

      • assocIn

        public static clojure.lang.IPersistentMap assocIn(clojure.lang.IPersistentMap m,
                                                  java.lang.Object value,
                                                  java.lang.String... keys)
        Similar to get-in and assoc, associates a key-value pair with a nested map. The value describes the value to place, and the string of keys describes a specific nesting order for which to place the value. The last key in the chain will be the one added as a key in the value-map of the second last key
        Parameters:
        m - The map in which to associate the key-value pair
        value - The value to be added to the nested map
        keys - The key chain specifying how to add the key-value pair
        Returns:
        The updated nested map

      • merge

        public static clojure.lang.IPersistentMap merge(clojure.lang.IPersistentMap m,
                                                clojure.lang.IPersistentMap m2)
        Merges two maps together, combining their key/value pairs. The result map will have a set of keys as (kset1 + kset2). Returns the new map.
        Parameters:
        m - First map to merge
        m2 - Second map to merge
        Returns:
        The merged map
